descriptions: We strongly extended the capabilities of the Nexus-e webviewer which is a tool used to visualize simulation results interactively and publicly accessible.
The Nexus-e software will be made open-source as a public git repository by the end of July 2025.
One energy system scenario with a detailed representation of the Swiss power system and relevant technological and economic parameters.
Implementation of a plugin architecture in Nexus-e.
New Python package to implement Nexus-e plugins on PyPI
Several meetings to share updates with the MOTEL project.
News entry on the Nexus-e website and on social media channels of the Energy Science Center at ETH Zürich about the open-sourcing of Nexus-e.
We have extended our network of collaboration partners by maintaining close contacts with the MOTEL project.
To this point, the improvements were only available internally at ETH Zürich for researchers at ESC, RRE, PSL and EPSE.
